34 void testOnce(std::string specName)
35 {
36  // setup the mixture
37  MixtureOptions mixture_options;
38  mixture_options.setThermodynamicDatabase("RRHO");
39  mixture_options.setSpeciesDescriptor(specName+"(*)");
40 
41  Mixture mix(mixture_options);
42 
43  const int ns = mix.nSpecies();
44 
45  Eigen::ArrayXd xi(ns);
46  Eigen::ArrayXd xth(ns);
47  Eigen::ArrayXd degen(ns);
48  Eigen::ArrayXd en(ns);
49 
50  // get the energy levels
51  IO::XmlDocument species_doc(databaseFileName("species.xml", "thermo"));
52 
53  ParticleRRHO spec(*(species_doc.root().findTagWithAttribute(
54  "species", "name", specName)->
55  findTagWithAttribute("thermodynamics", "type", "RRHO")));
56 
57  CHECK(spec.nElectronicLevels() == ns);
58 
59  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i) {
60  en[i] = spec.electronicEnergy(i).second;
61  degen[i] = spec.electronicEnergy(i).first;
62  }
63 
64  // check that levels follow the Boltzmann distribution at equilibrium
65  EQUILIBRATE_LOOP
66  (
67  // get the species mole fractions
68  xi = Eigen::Map<const Eigen::ArrayXd>(mix.X(), ns);
69 
70  double t1 = -1.0/T;
71 
72  // compute Boltzmann mole fractions
73  xth = degen*( (en*t1).exp() );
74  xth = xth/(xth.sum());
75  CHECK(xth.sum() == Approx(1.0));
76 
77  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i)
78  CHECK( xi[i] == Approx(xth[i]) );
79  )
80 
81 }
82 
83 TEST_CASE("Electronic levels are loaded properly using star token",
84  "[thermodynamics]"
85 )
86 {
87  testOnce("Ar");
88  testOnce("N");
89  testOnce("O2");
90 }
